{
  "text": "The concurrent administration of ATRA plus chemotherapy was supported by randomized trials demonstrating that patients who received both ATRA and chemotherapy had superior rates of CR and disease-free survival when compared with patients who received chemotherapy alone. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Moreover, the duration of coagulopathy was reduced when ATRA was added to induction chemotherapy. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] Furthermore, the addition of chemotherapy to ATRA helped to control hyperleukocytosis that occurred more frequently when ATRA was used alone. Therefore, the combination of ATRA plus chemotherapy limits complications that may occur when either agent is used alone.",
